         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne ¶ 13/3/74. ¶ To Mr. Webb Ware Esq. ¶  ¶ Act. Undersecretary &amp;c. ¶ Sir...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">74.03.13a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Thomas Ware</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">F74/3221, unit 737, VPRS 3991/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">13/3/74.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">To Mr. Webb Ware Esq.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Act. Undersecretary &amp;c.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In compliance with the request, conveyed in your letter of the 5th March,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See T. Ware to M, 5 March 1874.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I have the honor to transmit now herewith an estimate of the expenditure, which would be required for my Department during the coming financial year. I have deemed it my duty to provide fully for the efficient services of the institution under my control, but of course it is left to the consideration of the honorable the Chief Secretary, whether all the items recommended by me should be adopted. On comparison with the provision made for other scientific Departments it will be observed, that the permanent working fund deemed necessary by me is moderate, considering the multifarious information expected from my services, and considering that the Government is sure to desire a service advantageous to the country and honorable to myself. Should any special information yet be needed on any of the items, then I will not fail to afford it.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir, your obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd. von Mueller.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A memorandum with iillegible nitials accompanies M's letter: 'The accompanying Estimate received from the Gov. Botanist is exclusive of Public Works Estimate more than double the sum voted last year. Perhaps it would be advisable to obtain some expression of the Chief Secretary's views before placing any items for the Botanist on the pro forma copy of Estimates'.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">What was Chief Sec's response?</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>There is a further note in another hand: 'We have not paid any insts [instalments?] yet to purchase any<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>copy'.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Estimate of expenditure for the Department of the Gov. Botanist from July 1. 1874 to June 30. 1875.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">1,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Ordinary expenses</hi>
               </seg>.</p>
